          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Git AI does **not** use a command like `git notes ref-ai`. Authorship data is stored under the **`refs/notes/ai`** namespace, so you have to point `git notes` at that ref.\n\n### List notes (which commits have a note)\n\n```bash\ngit notes --ref=ai list\n```\n\n### Show the note for a specific commit\n\n```bash\ngit notes --ref=ai show <commit-sha>\n```\n\n### See commits with notes in the log\n\n```bash\ngit log --notes=ai\n```\n\n### Optional: show the notes ref Git is using\n\n```bash\ngit notes --ref=ai get-ref\n```\n\nThat should print something like `refs/notes/ai`.\n\n---\n\n**Why plain `git notes` is empty:** the default notes ref is `refs/notes/commits`. Git AI uses **`refs/notes/ai`** on purpose so it does not clash with other tools ([AGENTS.md](https://github.com/...) in your repo says the same).\n\n**Fetch/push:** to share notes, use the ref `refs/notes/ai` (e.g. `git fetch origin refs/notes/ai:refs/notes/ai` or configure remote tracking as your project documents).",
